Jenkins Brief:
- Jenkins is an open-source automation server used primarily for Continuous Integration (CI) and Continuous Deployment (CD). It helps automate the process of building, testing, and deploying code.

Key Features:
- Pipeline as Code: Define build workflows in a Jenkinsfile.
- Plugins: Over 1800 plugins to integrate with tools like Git, Docker.
- Extensible: Highly customizable through community plugins.
- Distributed Builds: Supports master agent architecture to distribute load across machines.
- Monitoring: Realtime build and test status dashboards.

Why Use Jenkins?
- Automates repetitive tasks like testing and deployment.
- Reduces integration problems by continuously merging code.
- Speeds up development with early bug detection and feedback.
- Works with almost any language or technology stack.

Real World Appliications
- Build automation (compiling code)
- Test automation (running unit/integration tests)
- Deploying applications (staging or production)
- Code quality analysis
